<hl>
<seg id=1> The retail index in August dropped 8.3% compared to the same period of last year. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> The retail index in August dropped 8.3% compared to the same period of last year, which is the 12th consecutive time this index has dropped. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> Since September 1997, the retail index has been dropping compared to the same periods of the years before, indicating that the local retail industry is still struggling to get out of its downturn. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> Compared to July of this year, the retail index dropped 8.3% </seg>
<seg id=5> If not including the sales of automobiles, the index dropped 3.9%. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> The statistics from the Department of statistics show that, almost all of the retail businesses were extremely weak in August. </seg>
<seg id=7> In July, the sales of automobiles increased 41.4%. However, in August they dropped 19.9%. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> The other retail businesses that decreased include: furniture and household products (8%), weaving and personal products (7.8%), department stores and supermarkets (2.6%), gas stations (1.3%), and general stores (0.3%). </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> On the other hand, the restaurant business also dropped 4.5% compared to the same period of last year, and it this was the 7th time in succession it has dropped since February 1998. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=10> However, if compared to July of this year, the restaurant business slightly increased by 1.4%. </seg>
<seg id=11> The money that people spent on food has approached 248 million Yuan, up from 245 million Yuan in July. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=12> The main reason for this increase is that the fast food business has increased 6.6%. </seg>
<seg id=13> The other restaurant businesses, excluding fast food, have also increased 2.5%. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=14> The Department of Statistics issues the numbers of the retail business and restaurant business index monthly, designed especially to find out the short-term performances in retail and restaurant businesses. </seg>
</p>
</DOC>
